1128
01:21:11,730 --> 01:21:12,291
[SPEAKER_07]: Let me tell you.

1129
01:21:12,311 --> 01:21:13,973
[SPEAKER_07]: OK.

1130
01:21:13,953 --> 01:21:15,156
[SPEAKER_07]: Let me tell you.

1131
01:21:15,176 --> 01:21:23,293
[SPEAKER_07]: In the summer of 2013, this government proposed action in Syria, the bombing of Syria, right?

1132
01:21:24,015 --> 01:21:31,371
[SPEAKER_07]: I was called into a room by David Cameron and Nick Clegg because President Obama had been on the phone, the leader of the free world, right?

1133
01:21:31,857 --> 01:21:36,783
[SPEAKER_07]: I listened to what they said, and over those days, I made up my mind, and we said no, right?

1134
01:21:37,203 --> 01:21:42,650
[SPEAKER_07]: Now, I think standing up to the leader of the free world, I think, shows a certain toughness, I would say.

1135
01:21:42,670 --> 01:21:44,252
[SPEAKER_07]: Are you proud of what's happened in Syria since?

1136
01:21:44,272 --> 01:21:45,393
[SPEAKER_07]: I'm not proud of it, no.

1137
01:21:45,514 --> 01:21:47,035
[SPEAKER_07]: It's a failure of the international community.

1138
01:21:47,176 --> 01:21:48,277
[SPEAKER_07]: But what I'm not going to...

1139
01:21:48,297 --> 01:21:49,338
[SPEAKER_07]: I'm not a pacifist.

1140
01:21:49,538 --> 01:21:54,264
[SPEAKER_07]: So I did support action in Libya, and David Cameron talked about how I supported action against ISIS.

1141
01:21:54,645 --> 01:21:56,707
[SPEAKER_07]: But am I tough enough?

1142
01:21:56,887 --> 01:21:57,969
[SPEAKER_07]: Hell, yes, I'm tough enough.

1143
01:21:59,831 --> 01:21:59,991
APPLAUSE

1144
01:22:02,536 --> 01:22:04,962
[SPEAKER_05]: Well, how has this impression got out there?

1145
01:22:05,063 --> 01:22:13,184
