1157
01:22:45,146 --> 01:22:47,628
[SPEAKER_07]: Look, Simon Danzig's entitled to his views.

1158
01:22:48,088 --> 01:22:53,073
[SPEAKER_07]: The only thing I can do, the thing I've learnt most in this job, let me tell you, is to be yourself, right?

1159
01:22:53,533 --> 01:22:54,294
[SPEAKER_07]: That's what I am.

1160
01:22:54,994 --> 01:22:56,816
[SPEAKER_07]: And, you know, people have to decide.

1161
01:22:56,836 --> 01:22:57,837
[SPEAKER_07]: Do they want my ideas?

1162
01:22:58,257 --> 01:22:59,438
[SPEAKER_07]: Do they want my principles?

1163
01:22:59,539 --> 01:23:07,906
[SPEAKER_07]: When I've stood up to not just the President Obama, but Rupert Murdoch, the energy companies, the banks, fighting for ordinary people, which is what I believe in and what I came into politics for.

1164
01:23:08,226 --> 01:23:12,710
[SPEAKER_07]: And do they want somebody who will think every day about how they put working people first in our country?

1165
01:23:12,850 --> 01:23:13,431
[SPEAKER_07]: And you know,

1166
